<title>USA: TABLE- Chris-Craft Q2 shr $0.31 vs $0.08.</title>
<headline>TABLE- Chris-Craft Q2 shr $0.31 vs $0.08.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Second quarter ended June 30</p>
<p>				1997			1996</p>
<p> Shr			  $0.31		    $0.08</p>
<p> Dil shr		     0.25		     0.07</p>
<p> Net			   10.0			2.7</p>
<p> Revs			 124.0		    125.0</p>
<p> Avg shrs		    31.9		     31.4</p>
<p>Six month ended June 30</p>
<p> Shr			  $2.66		    $0.09</p>
<p> Dil shr		     2.12		     0.08</p>
<p> Net			   85.2			3.1</p>
<p> Revs			 230.4		    231.2</p>
<p> Avg			   31.9		     31.4</p>
<p>(All data above in millions except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: Chris-Craft Industries Inc attributed the increase in 1997 net income primarily to a 53 percent reduction in the amount of United Paramount Network start-up losses to a $16.4 million loss (from a $35.0 million loss in Q2 1996).</p>
<p>The outstanding share and earnings per share figures reflect an April 1997 three percent stock dividend.</p>
